The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Controversies in cricket

Shoaib Akhtar and Mohammed Asif may be the latest to be embroiled in controversy, but crickets tryst with doping isnt new. The following is a list of players who have been involved in such controversies: 

 Ian Botham in 1986 for smoking cannabis suspended briefly 

 Pakistanis Wasim Akram, Waqar Younis, Aaqib Javed and Mushtaq Ahmed were accused of possession of marijuana in the West Indies in 1992-93 

 Ed Giddins (Sussex and England) was charged with use of cocaine in 1996 banned for 20 months from first-class cricket 

 South Africans Herschelle Gibbs, Roger Telemachus, Paul Adams, Justin Kemp and Andre Nel were accused of smoking marijuana in the West Indies in 2001 

 Shane Warne tested positive for diuretics in a test by Cricket Australia in 2003 was banned for a year 




